WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.759
In this episode of Detail, I'm really looking at opportunities to put pressure on the Cleveland

00:00:05.759 --> 00:00:07.839
defense by pushing hard in transition.

00:00:11.839 --> 00:00:16.240
Got to slow that one down. I know that in transition,

00:00:16.240 --> 00:00:18.719
Brian is always going to let the ball handler go by.

00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:21.760
He's always going to let you go by him.

00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:27.440
All right, he's always going to do this. He's going to slow down, he's going to let you go

00:00:27.440 --> 00:00:30.480
by him, and then he's going to catch you at the run.

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:35.520
Right. So that means in this situation,

00:00:38.079 --> 00:00:42.000
we have to recognize this. This is Terry over here. This is me with the ball,

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:46.400
Brian's here to make this penetration. Terry's got to know that Brian's going to allow this

00:00:46.400 --> 00:00:50.880
to happen. You know, which he wants the opportunity to contest late at the run.

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:55.600
So that means when this happens, I need to slide all the way down here in the corner.

00:00:56.399 --> 00:01:01.039
And now, you know, Terry slides all the way down in the corner, and now I can make that pass to Terry

00:01:02.800 --> 00:01:07.200
down in the corner for a shot. You know, Cleveland, it's a massive emphasis for them

00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:13.920
to get back on defense, right? So this penetration here really needs to be a bait,

00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:19.920
because now I can pull everybody in, right? I have four defensive players here

00:01:19.920 --> 00:01:24.640
concerned about the action that's taking place. I have Horford trailing, you know,

00:01:24.640 --> 00:01:28.560
Tristan's doing a great job. They'll stand between me and Horford and plugging up that line.

00:01:30.400 --> 00:01:33.120
JR is doing a great job running and getting on the line to tatum.

00:01:34.239 --> 00:01:39.359
LeBron is setting himself up to get a chase down block. Terry's got to make sure he's

00:01:39.359 --> 00:01:44.799
moving actively down here in the corner, and I got to be the one that's the bait, right?

00:01:44.799 --> 00:01:48.480
So I got to bait this drive here, and now I can find Terry here in the corner for three.

00:01:55.040 --> 00:02:01.840
You know, on the road, I have to make sure that we're all running together,

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:07.120
right? My speed here, here we go in the attack. You know, Cleveland's going to make a concerted

00:02:07.120 --> 00:02:09.920
effort to get back in transition, right? So they're going to build a wall.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:14.719
They're going to make sure everybody's back in the paint. They don't want to give us any

00:02:14.719 --> 00:02:18.960
fast break opportunities. Therefore, on this thrust, I got to make sure I have

00:02:18.960 --> 00:02:24.960
all my teammates are down with me in shooting positions. So when I collapse the defense,

00:02:24.960 --> 00:02:28.000
they're in position to shoot that ball or make a play for someone else.

00:02:28.560 --> 00:02:30.800
The guy get everybody moving, everybody running.

00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:36.319
If I can push hard in transition, put a lot of pressure on the defense that collapses

00:02:36.319 --> 00:02:40.640
the defense. Now, once the defense collapses, then it becomes my responsibility to find

00:02:40.640 --> 00:02:46.400
shooters on a perimeter. My ability to carry the thrust in transition, make or miss,

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:50.080
puts a lot of pressure on that Cleveland defense, then it becomes my responsibility

00:02:50.080 --> 00:02:53.840
once I get in the paint to make the proper reads. That's something I'd certainly look to

00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:58.879
take advantage of. Use our youth, our athleticism, to push hard at Cleveland in transition,

00:02:58.879 --> 00:03:16.240
especially on the road. For more analysis, go to detail on ESPN Plus.

